  "id": "ryouma",
  "name": "Ryouma",
  "title": "Warrior of the Nameless Beast",
  "description": "The ancient dragons of Erden bore grand names: Fornaxos, Kaidaros, Altaireon, Diabolos. All were silenced when the Goddess came, never to be spoken again. Only the dragon who slithered between the stars survived to see the new world.\n\nRyouma located this beast in his mountain lair, determined to prove his blade could best a dragon. He gave the beast a good fight, but in the end, could not overcome his nimble grace and speed. Satisfied with his effort, he submitted himself to a warrior's death, certain no one he left behind would miss him.\n\nThe dragon, having glimpsed the young warrior's true potential, refused to kill him, and instead made him his apprentice.",
